---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="For Business" description="Security perimeter for teams that vibe-code. Audits, monitoring, and compliance reports.">

<section class="hero">
  <h1>For Business</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">
    Your team vibe-codes. That is great for speed.
    But someone needs to make sure they are not shipping prompt injections
    to production. That someone is us.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>The problem</h2>
  <p>
    AI-assisted coding is everywhere. Your developers use Claude, Copilot, Cursor,
    or a dozen other tools to write code faster than ever.
    That is genuinely wonderful &mdash; until it is not.
  </p>
  <p>
    AI agents can be tricked into executing malicious commands.
    They can accidentally expose credentials. They can write code
    that looks correct but contains subtle vulnerabilities.
    Traditional security tools were not built for this. They scan code
    after it is written. By then, the damage is done.
  </p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <p>
    We create a security perimeter around your vibe coders.
    Not the kind that slows them down &mdash; the kind they barely notice.
  </p>

  <h3>Real-time protection</h3>
  <p>
    Safe Space hooks into AI coding agents and intercepts dangerous commands
    <em>before</em> they execute. If an AI agent tries to read your
    <code>.env</code> file and pipe it somewhere, we block it. Instantly.
    Your developer keeps coding. They might not even notice it happened
    (but you will, because it is in the report).
  </p>

  <h3>Session forensics</h3>
  <p>
    Every AI coding session generates logs. Nobody reads them.
    We do. Our scanner analyzes session logs for signs of prompt injection,
    credential access, unauthorized file modifications, and suspicious patterns.
    You get a clear, readable report &mdash; not a wall of CVE numbers.
  </p>

  <h3>Compliance dashboard</h3>
  <p>
    Your security team (or your boss, or your auditor) gets a dashboard showing
    which developers have Safe Space installed, what threats were detected,
    and what was blocked. Green means good. Red means someone has a conversation
    to have.
  </p>
  <p>
    <span class="tag">coming soon</span>
  </p>

  <h3>Zero-friction deployment</h3>
  <p>
    Your developers install Safe Space with a single command. It hooks into their
    existing AI coding tools automatically. No configuration files. No training sessions.
    No "security awareness workshops" that everyone hates.
    They install it, forget about it, and keep vibing.
  </p>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="section">
  <h2>Pricing</h2>

  <div class="pricing-grid">
    <div class="pricing-card">
      <h3>Individual</h3>
      <div class="price">Free</div>
      <p>For solo vibe coders who want peace of mind.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>All scanning features</li>
        <li>Real-time hook guard</li>
        <li>Session log analysis</li>
        <li>HTML reports</li>
        <li>Community support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="pricing-card">
      <h3>Team</h3>
      <div class="price">$9 <span>/ seat / month</span></div>
      <p>For teams that want visibility without bureaucracy.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Everything in Individual</li>
        <li>Team dashboard</li>
        <li>Centralized reporting</li>
        <li>Slack notifications</li>
        <li>Priority support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="pricing-card">
      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <div class="price">Let's talk</div>
      <p>For organizations with compliance requirements.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Everything in Team</li>
        <li>Custom policy rules</li>
        <li>SSO integration</li>
        <li>Audit trail export</li>
        <li>Dedicated support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<hr />

<section class="section">
  <h2>Get started</h2>
  <p>
    Install Safe Space on one machine. See what it catches.
    Then decide if your whole team needs it.
    No sales calls required.
  </p>

  <div class="prompt-box" id="biz-prompt">
    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyPrompt()">copy</button>I want to evaluate Chill.ai Safe Space for my team.

Our setup:
- Team size: [number] developers
- AI tools we use: [Claude Code / Cursor / Copilot / other]
- OS mix: [macOS / Windows / Linux]
- Main concern: [security compliance / credential protection / all of the above]

Please help me plan a pilot deployment. Walk me through
installing Safe Space on my machine first, then outline
how to roll it out to the team. Keep it simple.</div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
function copyPrompt() {
  const el = event.target.closest('.prompt-box');
  const text = el.textContent.replace('copy', '').trim();
  navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
  const btn = el.querySelector('.copy-btn');
  btn.textContent = 'copied';
  setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = 'copy', 2000);
}
</script>

</Base>
